author: Eric Yep
title: Crude-Oil Futures Slightly Higher Ahead of U.S. Jobs Data
text: 0131 GMT [Dow Jones] Crude-oil futures are slightly higher in early Asian trade Friday as traders position themselves ahead of today’s U.S. jobs report. Oil prices had slipped in the overnight session on weak equity markets and weaker-than-expected U.S. manufacturing data that weighed on sentiment. “However, fundamentals also remain weak,” ANZ says, with data showing a rise in U.S. inventory and an unexpected rise in production levels. “We continue to see weaker fundamentals drive crude oil prices lower in the short term,” it says.
